==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Midnight
<hw>Mid"night`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>midniht</ets>.]</ety> <def>The middle of the night; twelve o'clock
at night.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The iron tongue of <qex>midnight</qex> hath told twelve.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midnight</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Midnight
<hw>Mid"night`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being in, or characteristic of,
the middle of the night; <as>as, <ex>midnight</ex> studies;
<ex>midnight</ex> gloom.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Midnight</xex> shout and
revelry.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midnight sun</ent>⟦br⟧
